               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_15661-item1"
                          class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083116 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158">
                     <author>Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqīمحمد مهدی بن علی نقی</author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Zād al-musāfirīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">زاد المسافرين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A guide to preservation of health and self-treatment for travellers, by Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqī. The work was completed at Isfahan in 1141/1728, during the Afghan invasion, for<persName role="patron" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mīrzā Muḥammad Ismā‘īl</persName>.</p>
                        <p>It comprises two parts (maṭlab): on preventive health and hygiene, and on the treatment of certain ailments treatable without the aid of a physician.</p>
                        <p>The present manuscript is slightly incomplete at the end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
